<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-648-522  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 648 522.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  July 16 1990 v24 n29 p113(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Maintenance is looking good: as a career, it offers challenge,education, stability and healthy pay. (Computer Careers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ruhl, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The career opportunities in the software systems maintenance fieldare considerably brighter than is commonly believed.andP;  A survey of124 programmers and managers attending the annual SoftwareMaintenance Assn conference reveals that salaries and promotionopportunities, as well as job security, are excellent.andP;  The mediansalary of maintenance professionals, according to this survey, was$49,000.andP;  In terms of job security and promotions, 68 percentreported having been in the software maintenance field for morethan ten years.andP;  Two-thirds of the group reported a promotionwithin the past two years.andP;  The maintenance field tends tocultivate a variety of marketable skills, since maintenanceprofessionals interact with both technical support people and endusers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Software MaintenanceComputer IndustryCareersMaintenance ContractsSoftware Maintenance Association.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>